main event: A group of civilian astronomers observed four diffuse objects moving overhead at high speed in Miami, Florida on January 25, 1962.
interesting points: The objects were described as cigar-shaped, approximately the size of a second magnitude star, and appeared to be traveling at the speed of a jet aircraft.
The objects were observed to wobble or oscillate in their flight pattern, but no colored lights were seen.
The entire sighting lasted for approximately 2 minutes.
The observers concluded the objects were not terrestrial in nature and were unable to identify them as any known aircraft, weather balloon, meteor, or satellite.
A photograph was taken of what was believed to be the track of one of the unidentified objects, but analysis was inconclusive.
photographs: yes, one photograph was taken but analysis was inconclusive
